As a singer, rapper, and dancer, he effortlessly blends different styles and genres, showcasing his immense range and skill in every project he takes on. His ability to express complex emotions through his voice is unmatchedâ€”whether he's delivering a powerful rap verse or a hauntingly beautiful melody, Taeyong's vocal delivery always strikes a deep chord with his audience. His choreography is equally impressive, with his precision, fluidity, and ability to convey emotion through movement making him stand out as a performer. Beyond his musical talents, Taeyong's creativity as an artist shines through in his songwriting, where he explores personal themes and emotions, often offering deep insights into his thoughts and experiences. His dedication to pushing boundaries, both artistically and visually, is evident in every music video, performance, and project he undertakes. With a unique and magnetic stage presence, Taeyong has the rare ability to captivate and connect with fans on a profound level, making him not just an artist, but a true visionary in the entertainment industry. His fearless approach to self-expression and his constant drive for growth make him one of the most remarkable and influential figures in modern music.

I wrote the words below very quickly as a response to a critical comment on this MV from yesterday, but as it does represent how I really feel about 404 File Not Found and the series, I thought Iâ€™d post it here for more visibility  â€œNot long ago, I discussed Taeyongâ€™s lyrics for 404 File Not Found at a class I was at, because we were invited to discuss a piece of artwork that was inspiring to us .  I chose this song in order to explain how the metaphor of a 404 page loading error on the internet represented the idea of not being able to find yourself.    I discussed how this metaphor was particularly poignant and meaningful because of it being written by an idol and someone whose online celebrity identity no doubt becomes blurry at times in relation to the true, internal self. I also said I thought it was very brave for a kpop idol to write lyrics that reference mental health concerns, even obliquely, in their solo debut album.   I think the 404 series, just like all of Taeyongâ€™â€™s B-sides, represents the true work of patience, artistry, and deep personal reflection.   I think itâ€™s even more tremendous that Taeyong has been willing to invest 4 years into writing and releasing the 404 songsâ€¦. and that he even has the humility to present them just as B-sides, where they will not be promoted.   Such songs will simply remain quietly available  to a smaller audience who, if they have the time and openness, have the chance to hear his voice, one of the clearest and most courageous I have heard among pop artists.â€

Fact - Taeyong is charting domestically on MelOn, Bugs, Genie. His iTunes have the best charting record, Line and QQ music too. His MV is trending in both SK and Globally also on YT, Spotify and Apple Music. SM was notorious for TAP promotions more than Shalala. They squeezed this CB b/w Ten and NCT Wish. Giving the other two a promo of 19 days and 21 days but Taeyong with only 8 days. They posted TAP teasers late without using NCT, NCT127 and then immediately dumped photos of NCT Wish, Ten and SMTown to reduce visibility of his teasers. They didn't do P.O. and didn't included links for his album on Teasers. Taeyong had got only 5 promotions and one of them is of his friend and one of distant cousin. Shalala got two show promotions, no variety show as well. All this promotions are 7 shows for both albums still far less than NCT Ten, second soloist who got more than him combined on First day.  His first day sales are 128k without physical sales even in Korea and Globally as SM released physicals a day later. And SM didn't stock his album even though Shalala had 300k+ orders on first day.   So TAP is successful because he is Taeyong not like others whom company give YT Ads, Spotify Ads even on Twitter. They didn't send him on Multiple shows like Ten and he got the least days of promo in SM history with a worse rollout but he is charting on  MelOn, Bugs, Genie,Spotify, YouTube, iTunes. QQ music ( China ) and Awa and LINE ( Japanese ) bcoz of his skills, charisma and loyal fandom

Beats like a heartbeat, a rhythm so bold, "TAP," the title track, a story unfolds. Catchy the chorus, it sticks in your head, Lyrics like riddles, playfully said.  Feigning indifference, a nonchalant air, But deep down the feelings, a secret they share. Taeyong delivers, with wit and with charm, A message of confidence, weathering the storm.  Easy to sing along, the words flow so free, A soundtrack for dreamers, who long to be. Unburdened by expectations, they break from the mold, Embracing their spirit, stories untold.  So tap to the rhythm, let your heart take flight, Embrace what makes you different, and shine ever so bright.  "Let's do whatever we want," the anthem rings true, In the melody's magic, find your own point of view.

Cara membuat dangoÂ  Campurkan tepung beras, tepung beras ketan, dan gula. Tuang air panas sedikit demi sedikit. Campurkan hingga adonan mengental. Tutup mangkuk kemudian uleni adonan. Gunakan microwave atau kompor untuk memanaskan adonan tepung. Bagi adonan ke dalam tiga mangkuk. Beri pewarna makanan. Aduk-aduk dan bentuk bulat seperti bola. Tusukkan tiga dalam tusuk sate bambu. Hidangkan sebagai camilan manis.
